name: (E)-4-hydroxy-3-methylbut-2-enyl-diphosphate synthase (flavodoxin)
classes: Acting on CH or CH2 groups;
With an iron-sulfur protein as acceptor
reaction: (E)-4-hydroxy-3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl diphosphate + H2O + oxidized flavodoxin = 2-C-methyl-D-erythritol 2,4-cyclodiphosphate + reduced flavodoxin [RN:R10859]
comment: A bacterial iron-sulfur protein that contains a [4Fe-4S] cluster. Forms part of an alternative non-mevalonate pathway for isoprenoid biosynthesis that is found in most bacteria [2]. Plants and cyanobacteria have a similar enzyme that utilizes ferredoxin rather than flavodoxin (cf. EC 1.17.7.1).

references.title: Studies on the nonmevalonate pathway to terpenes: the role of the GcpE (IspG) protein.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 98 (2001) 14837-42.

references.title: Biosynthesis of isoprenoids. purification and properties of IspG protein from Escherichia coli.
fldA is an essential gene required in the 2-C-methyl-D-erythritol 4-phosphate pathway for isoprenoid biosynthesis.
